<para os = "solaris">These functions are for Solaris Security Toolkit (also known as JASS) driver functionality. These functions are in the <filename>driver.funcs</filename> file, located in the Drivers directory. Functions such as <filename>add_pkg</filename> and <filename>copy_a_file</filename> are in this file.</para>
<para os = "solaris">When customizing or creating scripts, use the following functions to perform standard operations:<itemizedlist
    mark = "bullet" spacing = "normal"><listitem os = "solaris"><para os = "solaris"><filename>add_patch</filename></para></listitem>
<listitem os = "solaris"><para os = "solaris"><filename>add_pkg</filename></para></listitem>
<listitem os = "solaris"><para os = "solaris"><filename>add_to_manifest</filename></para></listitem>
<listitem os = "solaris"><para os = "solaris"><filename>backup_file</filename></para></listitem>
<listitem os = "solaris"><para os = "solaris"><filename>check_os_main_version</filename></para></listitem>
<listitem os = "solaris"><para os = "solaris"><filename>check_os_revision</filename></para></listitem>
<listitem os = "solaris"><para os = "solaris"><filename>copy_a_dir</filename></para></listitem>
<listitem os = "solaris"><para os = "solaris"><filename>copy_a_file</filename></para></listitem>
<listitem os = "solaris"><para os = "solaris"><filename>copy_a_symlink</filename></para></listitem>
<listitem os = "solaris"><para os = "solaris"><filename>copy_files</filename></para></listitem>
<listitem os = "solaris"><para os = "solaris"><filename>create_a_file</filename></para></listitem>
<listitem os = "solaris"><para os = "solaris"><filename>create_file_timestamp</filename></para></listitem>
<listitem os = "solaris"><para os = "solaris"><filename>disable_conf_file</filename></para></listitem>
<listitem os = "solaris"><para os = "solaris"><filename>disable_file</filename></para></listitem>
<listitem os = "solaris"><para os = "solaris"><filename>disable_rc_file</filename></para></listitem>
<listitem os = "solaris"><para os = "solaris"><filename>is_patch_applied</filename></para></listitem></itemizedlist></para>
<para os = "solaris">For detailed information and instructions on the use of each of these functions please refer to the "Framework Functions" chapter of the <citetitle pubwork = "book">&SST-REFMAN;</citetitle>.</para></refsect1>
<refsect1 os = "solaris"><title>&exam-tt;</title>
<example width = "100" os = "solaris"><title>Adding a Single Patch</title><screen width = "100" format = "linespecific">
add_patch 123456-01
</screen></example>
<example width = "100" os = "solaris"><title>Adding a Patch List</title><screen width = "100" format = "linespecific">
add_patch -M ${JASS_PATCH_DIR}/OtherPatches patch_list.txt
</screen></example></refsect1>
